|| R E A D M E ||
¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯

Dolly use Apache Maven to build Java code and CMake to generate Makefile to build C++ code.
Software requirements specification:
	* compatible Java5 JDK version
	* CMake
	* C++ compiler
	* Apache Ant 
	* Apache Maven


| HOWTO BUILD DOLLY DISTRIBUTION |
¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
	Generate Makefile to build C++ code (only first time):
	
		$ cd dolly-core
		$ cmake .
	
	Create distribution:
	
		$ ant


| HOWTO SETUP AN ECLIPSE DEVELOPMENT ENVIROMENT |
¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯¯
	Set a new variable in Preferences ::-> Java -> Build path -> Classpath variables as
		name: M2_REPO
		path: /path/to/maven/repository
		
	Use maven to setup eclipse project
	
		$ mvn eclipse:eclipse
	
	Import the two distinct project from File ::-> Import -> Existing project
	
		dolly-core
		dolly-clone
		
	Generate Makefile to build C++ code:
	
		$ cd dolly-core
		$ cmake .
